(107, 1, '2013-11-12 06:06:22', '2013-11-12 06:06:22', 'Major sources of quantifiable benefits from the project interventions are: increase in crop productivity; decrease in agricultural production variability; reduced production costs; and increase in milk, meat, egg and fish productivity in the targeted House Holds. The project will also introduce variety in cropping patterns and environment friendly resource utilization. The direct beneficiaries of the project are about 300,000 farmers, especially the small and marginal farmers in more challenging agro-ecological zones.\r\n\r\n<small>[contactimplementation]</small>\r\n\r\nApproximately 25% of the direct beneficiaries are expected to be women farmers. Beyond these, there are other indirect beneficiaries, i.e. farmers who will, following demonstration effects over time, adopt technologies and practices used by project-supported farmers and rural agricultural labourers.', 'Project Benefits', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'project-benefits', '', '', '2013-12-01 14:42:44', '2013-12-01 14:42:44', '', 0, 'http://localhost/iapp/?page_id=107', 19, 'page', '', 0),
